JOHANNESBURG - Former Eastern Province Kings' President Daniel 'Cheeky' Watson was arrested by the Hawks on Friday morning and faces charges of corruption and money laundering.#UPDATE Cheeky Watson and his co-accused have been released on R2000 bail pic.twitter.com/AfG8nH8RRlHe was released on R2000 bail from New Law Courts.Former EPRU President Cheeky Watson has been released on R2000 bail from New Law Courts. He faces charges of corruption & money launderingWatson is known for being one of the first white South African rugby union players to participate in a mixed race rugby game during the apartheid era when mixed-race activities were outlawed by apartheid legislation.He is also the father of controversial former Springbok number 8 Luke Watson. eNCA